=== COMPREHENSIVE TESTING INSTRUCTIONS ===
Ensure your test suite covers the following areas where applicable to the feature functionality:

1. Functional Testing:
   - Installation/Uninstallation: Verify app installs, launches, and uninstalls without leaving garbage files.
   - Interrupt Testing: Check app behavior during incoming calls, SMS, push notifications, battery low alerts, or screen locking.
   - Navigation & Form Validation: Ensure all buttons, input fields, and links work as intended.
   - Background/Foreground: Test functionality when the app is minimized and resumed.

2. UI/UX Testing:
   - Orientation: Check layout consistency when switching between portrait and landscape modes.
   - Responsiveness: Verify user interface elements scale correctly across different screen sizes.
   - Gesture Testing: Test swipe, pinch, zoom, and long-press functionalities.

3. Performance Testing:
   - Load/Stress Testing: Assess app speed, responsiveness, and stability under heavy usage.
   - Battery & Resource Usage: Ensure the app does not drain battery excessively or consume too much memory.
   - Network Speed: Verify performance under varying network conditions (3G, 4G, 5G, Wi-Fi, offline).

4. Compatibility Testing:
   - Device/OS Coverage: Test on different OS versions and screen resolutions.
   - Browser Compatibility: Verify functionality in common browsers (Chrome, Safari).

5. Security Testing:
   - Data Storage: Check that sensitive data is encrypted and not stored locally in plain text.
   - Authentication: Validate login mechanisms, session timeout, and secure token management.

6. Localization & Environment Testing:
   - Time Zone/Language: Ensure the app displays correct date/time formats and localized text.
   - Push Notifications: Confirm push notifications are received and trigger correct in-app actions.

7. Network & Connectivity:
   - Offline Mode: Verify that the app handles offline states gracefully and caches data for later synchronization.
   - Throttled Network: Simulate 2G/3G speeds or high latency to test retry logic and loading indicators.
   - Airplane Mode: Validate that the app pauses tasks immediately and resumes once reconnected.

